  "prompt": "How do I reverse the words in a String without reversing each character and not using builtin functions like split and substring in C#?",
  "response": "To reverse the words in a string in C# without using built-in functions like `Split` and `Substring`, you need to manually process the string. Here's a step-by-step approach:\n\n1. Iterate through the string to identify the words.\n2. Store the start positions and lengths of the words.\n3. Construct a new string with the words in reverse order.\n\nHere's a sample implementation:\n\n```csharp\nusing System;\nusing System.Text;\n\nclass Program\n{\n    static void Main(string[] args)\n    {\n        string input = \"Hello World This Is CSharp\";\n        string result = ReverseWords(input);\n        Console.WriteLine(result);\n    }\n\n    static string ReverseWords(string input)\n    {\n        int length = input.Length;\n        List<(int start, int length)> words = new List<(int start, int length)>();\n\n        // Step 1: Identify words in the string and store their start positions and lengths\n        int wordStart = -1;\n        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++)\n        {\n            if (input[i] != ' ' && wordStart == -1)\n            {\n                wordStart = i;\n            }\n            else if ((input[i] == ' ' || i == length - 1) && wordStart != -1)\n            {\n                int wordEnd = (input[i] == ' ') ? i - 1 : i;\n                words.Add((wordStart, wordEnd - wordStart + 1));\n                wordStart = -1;\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Step 2: Build the result string with words in reverse order\n        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();\n        for (int i = words.Count - 1; i >= 0; i--)\n        {\n            (int start, int len) = words[i];\n            result.Append(input, start, len);\n            if (i != 0)\n            {\n                result.Append(' ');\n            }\n        }\n\n        return result.ToString();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nExplanation:\n\n1. **Identify words**: Iterate through the input string, track the start and end position of each word while skipping spaces.\n2. **Store words**: Save each word's start position and length in a list.\n3. **Reverse words order**: Using a `StringBuilder`, append each word in reverse order to construct the final string.\n\nThis code reverses the words in the provided string `input` without reversing the characters within the words and without using `Split` or `Substring` functions.",
